      • safeCallback

        protected <K> com.google.common.util.concurrent.FutureCallback<K> safeCallback(Callback<K> onSuccess,
                                                                               Callback<Throwable> onFailure)
        Generates a guava FutureCallback to attach to a ListenableFuture with given success and failure callbacks. Wraps the invocations such that if an uncaught runtime exception is thrown from a callback invocation, a warning is logged. Such a case must be seriously considered in an asynchronous system, as it can cause the system to freeze if some pending propagation has not reached before the exception was thrown.
        Type Parameters:
        K - type of the returned FutureCallback
        Parameters:
        onSuccess - callback on be invoked on success, or null to skip success event.
        onFailure - callback on be invoked on failure, or null to skip failure event.
        Returns:
        a guava FutureCallback to attach to a ListenableFuture
